cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on exploring surfaces and building compact 3D representations of the environment surrounding a robot through active perception. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper uses a PrimeSense camera for visual measurements. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes an online probabilistic framework that merges visual and tactile measurements using Gaussian Random Field and Gaussian Process Implicit Surfaces. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper proposes a framework for object detection and terrain classification. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves controlling a robotic arm equipped with tactile sensors.
